This paper is about navigational query languages for graphs, which is a topic that falls under the area of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the expressive power of different query languages, which is related to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a Hasse diagram, which is a tool used in combinatorics and graph theory (cs.CC).
